-- Mayroy sells 7 pct stake in Ipsen
-- By Lionel Laurent and Blaise Robinson
-- Wed Mar 19, 2014 01:00PM EDT
-- None



PARIS, March 19 (Reuters) - Mayroy, the biggest shareholder in French pharmaceutical company Ipsen <IPN.PA>, announced on Wednesday the sale of a 7 percent stake in Ipsen via private placement, bringing its stake down to 57.6 percent.

Price details were not disclosed but the announced sale of 5.89 million shares would be worth around 188 million euros ($261 million)at Wednesday's closing price of 32 euros per Ipsen share. Mayroy said Ipsen has said it plans to take part in the placement and purchase 842,000 shares for cancellation.